Docker Exercise: Multi-Container Web Application
Task: Create a simple web application with a Python Flask backend and Redis cache, running in separate containers.
Requirements:

Create a Flask application that:

Has an endpoint that counts page visits
Stores the visit count in Redis
Returns "Hello! This page has been visited X times"


Set up two containers:

One for the Flask app
One for Redis


Create the necessary files:

app.py - Your Flask application
requirements.txt - Python dependencies
Dockerfile - To containerize the Flask app
docker-compose.yml - To orchestrate both containers


Goals:

Containers should communicate with each other
The app should be accessible on http://localhost:5000
Visit count should persist as long as containers are running



Bonus Challenges:

Add volume mapping so Redis data persists even after container restart
Add environment variables for configuration
Implement health checks

